-> Frontend in 'client' folder
-> Backend in 'server' folder

FOR FRONTEND

1.  'npm init' to create package.json file
2.  Download npm express - 'npm i express'
3.  After writing code in app.js, in terminal type 'nodemon app.js' to run it
4.  Install Mongoose, 'npm i mongoose'
5.  If there is deprecation warning-

mongoose.connect(DB,{
    useNewUrlParser: true,
    userCreateIndex: true,
    useUnifiedTopology: true,
    useFindAndModify: false
}).then(()=>{
    console.log('connection successful');
}).catch((err) => console.log('no connection'))

6.  Install dotenv, 'npm i dotenv'
7.  For securing port number and key, type it in config.env and then add it to .gitignore
    Files in gitignore will not be displayed in github.

8.  mongoose.connect(DB).then(()=>{
    console.log('Connection successful');
    }).catch((err)=>console.log('No connection'));

    This part of code will be used freqently in many places so it has been added to './db/conn.js'

9.  User schema and model in userSchema.js
10. In postman, in headers, under Key type content-type and under Value set value of content-type as application/json
11. Install bcrypt.js dependency for hashing password
12. Install jsonwebtoken in server folder




1. Install cookie-parser in server folder(after backend and frontend are connected and u want to show the about page of the relevant user)
    Use- for sending the cookie recieved in frontend to backend
